  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Currently there is no intervention to prevent persistent postpartum hypertension in
      preeclamptic women. Physiologically, the use of a pharmacokinetically predictable
      loop-diuretic is a reasonable intervention to increase elimination of extra fluid accumulated
      secondary to preeclampsia.The purpose of this study is to assess if Torsemide reduces the
      incidence of persistent postpartum hypertension in preeclamptic women.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
